						<summary>

						<p>Parapet wall to the right of entrance into the Sabhāmaṇṭapa of the Sōmēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>12th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription, engraved above panel sculptures, states that the sculptures represent the exploits of Ēkāntada Rāmayya against the followers of the Jina. The characters are of about 12th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">Ep. Ind.,</hi> Vol. V, p. 260-61.</p>						

